13/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Jovan Manasijevski met with Serbia-Montenegro counterpart Prvoslav Davinic in Skopje on Tuesday (12 July), discussing defence reforms and participation in regional initiatives, as well as integration into Euro-Atlantic structures. 
Davinic noted Macedonia's progress in terms of reforms and the international integration process, suggesting such experience could be transferred to Serbia-Montenegro.
Also Tuesday, Skopje wrapped up a two-day conference of the Gnjilane-Presevo-Kumanovo-Trgoviste initiative. 
It encourages development and co-operation among neighbouring regions in southern Serbia, Kosovo and Macedonia. 
(MIA, Tanjug - 12/07/05)
